# Bun Usage in this Repository

Follow these conventions when running, building, or testing.

- Use `bun install` to install dependencies (not npm/pnpm/yarn)
- Use `bun run <script>` to run scripts from [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- Use `bun test` for tests (if present)
- Use `bun <file>` instead of `node <file>`
- Bun auto-loads `.env`; do not add `dotenv`

Server APIs and Databases (if needed in tooling code):

- Prefer `Bun.$` for shelling out
- Prefer `Bun.file` over fs read/write

This project is a Next.js app; you still use Next.js dev/build commands via Bun scripts, e.g. in [package.json](mdc:package.json):

```json
{
    "scripts": {
        "dev": "next dev",
        "build": "next build",
        "start": "next start -p 3000"
    }
}
```

Run with:

```bash
bun run dev
```
